snippet.textDisplay: After an incredible 3 years of living, working and traveling in our self converted Sprinter Van we’ve had to make the very tough decision to abandon our tiny home in Africa to take a rescue flight back to Canada.  As it has for so, so many of us, this global pandemic has absolutely flipped our world upside down. And while quarantining was going well for us it became apparent that things would be different for a long while.  When our Prime Minister announced that he was sending repatriation flights over to Africa to pick up Canadians who were stuck (due to border closures) we consulted with friends and family closest to us and realized that in this time of crisis we should be back in our home country. The gravity of what we’ve just done hasn’t quite sunk in and we ((especially me (Bec)) are having a really hard time adjusting to our new reality.  Having said that we think the most important thing we can all do now is STAY HOME, keep healthy with healing foods & try to look at this as a time that we (and the planet) desperately needed to reset and realign.  Sending each of you so much love throughout this time x

snippet.textDisplay:
Surely you'd be better off on the road in Africa rather than flying back to Canada?
As long as you have shelter, your van, food, if you can't buy locally, you could easily forage, fruit, sea food, fish, plants, veg etc etc and fresh water......you're sorted.?
I can tell you the situation here in the UK for example is very grim, food and essentials are still very low in the shops, queues for shops are horrendous, I see civil unrest looming, more chance of being infected as time goes by etc etc
If I had chance, I'd be cruising across Africa in a van away from this hellish situation. 👍😎
Take care, stay safe 👍😎⚠️😷😯
Edit- Hope you disconnected your batteries in the van otherwise they'll be toast when you go back for it⚠️😯

snippet.textDisplay: i just started my year living in a van in new zealand, and a few days ago i was lucky to move into a house with a lovely family & the friend i’m here in NZ with. i decided against going back to Canada, my home country, since i have a place to be here for the time being. 4 week lockdown here just started a few days ago! and it’s looking like it’ll be more than 4 weeks now. back home my sister has been laid off for 12 weeks minimum. it’s so strange. safer and calmer in NZ, less people, less cases... however my comment is only to say that i can relate in a way to having to give up the adventurous lifestyle,the wonder of exploring a new place on the road. it’s so sad and weird. life is weird right now. but this won’t last forever 🧡
